3. SYMLINK CONTAINMENT: filepath.EvalSymlinks(WorktreeDir) and EvalSymlinks(ScratchDir) (both exist by validation) BEFORE the filepath.Rel containment check, so a symlinked ScratchDir pointing inside WorktreeDir is caught. Test: symlinked ScratchDir resolving under WorktreeDir -> rejected.
4. CTX TAXONOMY: after exec, if ctx.Err() is context.Canceled/DeadlineExceeded, return an error for which errors.Is(err, context.Canceled/DeadlineExceeded) holds (wrap ctx.Err()), DISTINCT from ErrRunnerFailed. Test: already-cancelled ctx (or tiny deadline + sleep script) -> errors.Is(..., context.Canceled/DeadlineExceeded).
